We spent way too much time into this bug, but we have found a stripped-down example of the given code. We tested so many cases and often they were working repeatable, but sometimes they broke unexpected (debugging of the flutter engine in the browser is very very hard). 

Smallest code example with broken text input:

```import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/rendering.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const App());

  SemanticsBinding.instance.ensureSemantics();
}

class App extends StatelessWidget {
  const App({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const MaterialApp(
      home: TextDecorationExample(),
    );
  }
}

class TextDecorationExample extends StatelessWidget {
  const TextDecorationExample({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const Scaffold(
      body: Column(
        mainAxisSize: MainAxisSize.max,
        crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.stretch,
        children: [
          TextField(
            decoration: InputDecoration(
              errorText: 'error',
              hintText: 'hint',
              suffixIcon: Icon(Icons.abc),
            ),
            autofocus: true,
          ),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```
If we **unfocus** the TextField and **refocus** it, we can enter text.
Also if we change the **autofocus to false** or **remove one of errorText, hintText or suffixIcon**, we can enter text as expected.

_________________________________
We analyzed the behaviour of the flutter quill editor [https://pub.dev/packages/flutter_quill] with the flutter engine and the SemanticsTextEditingStrategy singleton, because we had our first problems with it while semantics was enabled. 

We found out that the SemanticsTextEditingStrategy._instance singleton is null for the second call (hasFocus = true) in this line https://github.com/flutter/engine/blob/main/lib/web_ui/lib/src/engine/semantics/text_field.dart#L439
So it seems that this line https://github.com/flutter/engine/blob/main/lib/web_ui/lib/src/engine/text_editing/text_editing.dart#L2304 was not called before building the TextField the first time.

So the activate https://github.com/flutter/engine/blob/main/lib/web_ui/lib/src/engine/semantics/text_field.dart#L71 method was not called for the first update. 

This behaviour does not apply to the stripped-down code example. Only for flutter quill.
____________________________________

The example of @jmandawg is working if we switch the Navigator and the TextBox. 
Example (not working):
```
children: [
  TextField(
    autofocus: false,
  ),
  Expanded(
    child: Navigator(
    key: _navigator,
    initialRoute: '/',
    onGenerateRoute: (settings) => OnChangedExampleApp.onGenerateRoutes()
    ),
  ),
],
```

Example (working):
```
children: [
  Expanded(
    child: Navigator(
    key: _navigator,
    initialRoute: '/',
    onGenerateRoute: (settings) => OnChangedExampleApp.onGenerateRoutes()
    ),
  ),
  TextField(
    autofocus: false,
  ),
],
```

We hope someone like @htoor3 or @dam-ease can take a look at this and will find a fix.

